  "response": "Yes, it is wrong to launder money. Here's why:\n\n*   **It's illegal:** Money laundering is a crime in virtually every country in the world. Laws are in place to combat it.\n*   **It supports criminal activity:** Money laundering helps criminals hide the proceeds of their illegal activities, allowing them to continue those activities. This includes drug trafficking, terrorism, human trafficking, and other serious crimes.\n*   **It harms the economy:** Money laundering can distort financial markets and undermine the stability of financial institutions. It can also lead to unfair competition and corruption.\n*   **It undermines the rule of law:** Money laundering allows criminals to operate outside the legal system, weakening the rule of law and eroding public trust in institutions.\n\nIn short, money laundering is wrong because it facilitates crime, harms the economy, and undermines the legal system.",
